data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533896\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 05, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104xsp1665702999134.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xsp1665702999134.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xsp1665702999134.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xsp1665702999134\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                    \n Prepare the Uniface 9 Application for Migration\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Prepare your Uniface 9 application for migration to Uniface 10 to avoid migration issues and functional changes to your application.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"xsp1665702999134__context_w3062ab1b5b1_w3063ab1b5_w3064ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xsp1665702999134__p_d68450e1_d68451e1_d68452e1\">Previous step: <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ikq1665702999204.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ikq1665702999204.html\" title=\"Before you begin to migrate your application, ensure that you fulfill the prerequisites and familiarize yourself the Migration Utility and the actions it takes.\">Prepare to Migrate from Uniface 9</a>\n</p>\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"xsp1665702999134__topic_d68453e1_d68454e1_d68455e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xsp1665702999134__p_d68456e1_d68457e1_d68458e1\">During migration to Uniface 10, Uniface will reject any part of an import if it detects non-migrated definitions coming from version 8.</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"xsp1665702999134__li_d31196e1_d31197e1_d31198e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Compile your application definitions from the command line, using the latest\n               Uniface 9.6 or 9.7 release. \n            </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"xsp1665702999134__li_d31199e1_d31200e1_d31201e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"xsp1665702999134__p_d68462e1_d68463e1_d68464e1\">Review the compiler messages and correct any\n               identified issues. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">The latest Uniface 9.7 release reports additional compiler warnings that indicate\n                  possible incompatibilities with Uniface 10:</p>\n<div class=\"note warning note_warning\" id=\"xsp1665702999134__p_d68465e1_d68466e1_d68467e1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Warning:</span>\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nax1665702999276.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nax1665702999276.html\" title=\"This compiler message is generated in Uniface 9 when duplicate entries are detected in the model and in the component.\">Warning: 1000 Entry EntryName from model overwrites definition from component. In future Uniface versions, this will be reversed</a>\n</div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"xsp1665702999134__li_d31202e1_d31203e1_d31204e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"xsp1665702999134__p_d68468e1_d68469e1_d68470e1\">Determine whether to migrate Uniface 9 defaults\n               to Uniface 10. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rpy1665702998477.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rpy1665702998477.html\" title=\"Uniface 9 used a default set of objects to create new objects. These are known as the Uniface defaults, and automatically loaded from the udefault.xml file the very first time the Uniface 9 Development Environment is started.\">Migration of Uniface 9 Defaults</a>. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">If necessary, correct your definitions to remove unnecessary dependencies to\n                  unused Include Procs.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"xsp1665702999134__li_d31205e1_d31206e1_d31207e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Run and test the migrated application in Uniface 9.\n </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n<section class=\"section result body required-cleanup-multiple-ol-elements-in-topic-body\" id=\"xsp1665702999134__result_w3065ab1b5b5_w3066ab1b5_w3067ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xsp1665702999134__p_d68471e1_d68472e1_d68473e1\">Next step: <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"spp1665702999061.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/spp1665702999061.html\" title=\"When your Uniface 9 application is ready to migrate, export the repository objects, then import into Uniface 10. Whenever Uniface detects that there are records that need to be migrated, it automatically starts the migration process. This may also occur if a previous migration process was interrupted.\">Migrate Repository Objects from Uniface 9</a>\n</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533896\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533896\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Prepare the Uniface 9 Application for Migration Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 05, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Prepare the Uniface 9 Application for Migration Prepare your Uniface 9 application for migration to Uniface 10 to avoid migration issues and functional changes to your application. Previous step: Prepare to Migrate from Uniface 9 During migration to Uniface 10, Uniface will reject any part of an import if it detects non-migrated definitions coming from version 8. Compile your application definitions from the command line, using the latest Uniface 9.6 or 9.7 release. Review the compiler messages and correct any identified issues. The latest Uniface 9.7 release reports additional compiler warnings that indicate possible incompatibilities with Uniface 10: Warning: Warning: 1000 Entry EntryName from model overwrites definition from component. In future Uniface versions, this will be reversed Determine whether to migrate Uniface 9 defaults to Uniface 10. For more information, see Migration of Uniface 9 Defaults . If necessary, correct your definitions to remove unnecessary dependencies to unused Include Procs. Run and test the migrated application in Uniface 9. Next step: Migrate Repository Objects from Uniface 9 Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}